WEBVTT

00:04.137 --> 00:05.272
OH, GOOD.

00:05.272 --> 00:07.975
I WAS HOPING I COULDN'T PUT
ANYTHING ON THE TABLE.

00:07.975 --> 00:10.110
YOU NEED THE TABLE
TO PUT YOUR FLOOR SAMPLES ON?

00:10.110 --> 00:12.246
JUST PUT THEM ON THE FLOOR.

00:12.246 --> 00:15.048
FELIX, LEAVE HER ALONE.
SHE'S GOT A LOT OF WORK TO DO.

00:15.048 --> 00:16.283
SHE'S IN CHARGE
OF PUTTING TOGETHER

00:16.283 --> 00:18.051
HER COMPANY'S
CHARITY WALKATHON.

00:18.051 --> 00:20.053
WALKING FOR MONEY.

00:20.053 --> 00:25.292
IN MY VILLAGE,
YOU'D WALK 12 MILES FOR <i>A STICK.</i>

00:27.060 --> 00:29.062
I THINK WE ALL KNOW
WHERE YOU KEPT IT.

00:34.001 --> 00:37.037
EXCUSE ME.
I HAVE AN ANNOUNCEMENT.

00:37.037 --> 00:39.206
OOH,
STAND BACK, EVERYBODY.

00:39.206 --> 00:41.341
THE HANDSOME MAYOR
HAS SOMETHING TO SAY.

00:41.341 --> 00:44.278
I HAVE CHOSEN WHO I WANT TO BE
MY CONFIRMATION SPONSOR.

00:44.278 --> 00:46.179
OH, IS IT ME?
IT'S PROBABLY ME.

00:46.179 --> 00:48.248
BECAUSE YOU LOVE ME, RIGHT?
NO PRESSURE.

00:48.248 --> 00:51.318
DAD, AGAIN,
IT CAN'T BE A PARENT.

00:51.318 --> 00:53.353
ARE YOU SURE?
THERE'S A NEW POPE.

00:53.353 --> 00:55.122
A LOT OF CHANGES.

00:55.122 --> 00:56.156
IT'S CRISTELA.

00:56.156 --> 00:57.991
AAH! YES!

00:57.991 --> 00:59.059
[ LAUGHS ]

00:59.059 --> 01:00.327
NOW I HAVE THE TABLE
AND YOUR KID.

01:00.327 --> 01:03.263
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

01:03.263 --> 01:04.364
CONGRATULATIONS, CRISTELA.

01:04.364 --> 01:06.366
I LOOK FORWARD
TO BE WORKING WITH YOU.

01:06.366 --> 01:08.969
OH, THANK YOU, SIR.

01:08.969 --> 01:11.104
IT'S FINE.
I'LL BE IN THE GARAGE.

01:11.104 --> 01:14.174
THERE'S A TABLE THERE,
AND IT'S ALL MINE.

01:14.174 --> 01:18.111
IT'S A WORKBENCH.
EVERYBODY KNOWS THAT.

01:18.111 --> 01:19.246
CRIS,
ARE YOU SURE YOU CAN DO THIS?

01:19.246 --> 01:21.315
YOU ALREADY HAVE
A LOT GOING ON.

01:21.315 --> 01:25.252
PLUS, YOU'RE ONLY
KIND OF A CATHOLIC.

01:25.252 --> 01:29.122
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
I GO TO CHURCH.

01:29.122 --> 01:31.224
WHEN IT'S NOT
FOOTBALL SEASON.

01:33.260 --> 01:36.196
DO YOU EVEN KNOW
WHAT YOU HAVE TO DO?

01:36.196 --> 01:39.232
UH, I KNOW ENOUGH
TO LOOK IT UP ON THE INTERNET.

01:39.232 --> 01:42.002
RELAX.

01:42.002 --> 01:44.104
I-I KNOW I'M NOT AS GUNG HO
AS YOU, <i>AMA,</i>

01:44.104 --> 01:46.306
BUT I TAKE
MY FAITH SERIOUSLY.

01:46.306 --> 01:48.208
UH-HUH.

01:48.208 --> 02:00.020
WE BOTH KNOW BETTER,
DON'T WE?

02:00.020 --> 02:01.254
YOU KNOW WHAT, HENRY?

02:01.254 --> 02:03.256
THREE GENERATIONS
OF GONZALEZ MEN

02:03.256 --> 02:06.226
HAVE WORN THAT SUIT
TO THEIR CONFIRMATION CEREMONY.

02:06.226 --> 02:08.261
AND NOW IT'S YOUR TURN
TO STAND UP

02:08.261 --> 02:10.998
IN FRONT OF
ALL OUR FRIENDS AND FAMILY

02:10.998 --> 02:12.265
IN THIS HIDEOUS SUIT.

02:14.034 --> 02:16.269
HENRY, STOP MOVING.

02:16.269 --> 02:19.106
YOU'RE LIKE A RACCOON
IN A BURLAP SACK,

02:19.106 --> 02:22.042
WHICH IS HOW YOUR UNCLE ARTEMIO
CAME TO THIS COUNTRY.

02:22.042 --> 02:24.011
HEY.

02:24.011 --> 02:25.178
THAT'S RIGHT.

02:25.178 --> 02:28.348
WITH A RACCOON
INSIDE A BURLAP SACK.

02:30.150 --> 02:31.218
STOP.

02:31.218 --> 02:33.353
BUT THIS SUIT
IS SO ITCHY.
AY!

02:33.353 --> 02:35.989
HOW DOES
ELLEN DeGENERES DO IT?

02:37.357 --> 02:41.261
OH, CRIS, WILL YOU BE ABLE TO
MAKE IT TO THE PANCAKE BREAKFAST

02:41.261 --> 02:43.096
BEFORE WE HEAD ON
OUT TO THE CHURCH?

02:43.096 --> 02:46.066
NO, I CAN'T.
THE WALKATHON IS IN THE MORNING.

02:46.066 --> 02:47.234
WELL,
YOU ARE HIS SPONSOR.

02:47.234 --> 02:48.335
IT WOULD BE NICE

02:48.335 --> 02:50.337
IF YOU COULD MAKE IT
TO HENRY'S BREAKFAST, TOO.

02:50.337 --> 02:53.306
HEY, DON'T MAKE ME
FEEL GUILTY.

02:53.306 --> 02:56.076
YOU THINK
I LIKE MISSING PANCAKES?

02:58.111 --> 03:02.015
YES, DON'T MAKE HER FEEL GUILTY,
DANIELA.

03:02.015 --> 03:05.318
THAT'S WHAT HAPPENS WHEN A
SPONSOR DOESN'T CARE ABOUT GOD.

03:07.287 --> 03:09.356
HEY, I GOT THIS.

03:09.356 --> 03:10.390
HUH?

03:10.390 --> 03:13.093
AFTER THE WALKATHON,
I'LL GO TO CHURCH.

03:13.093 --> 03:14.261
THAT'S WHAT I DO,
YOU KNOW?

03:14.261 --> 03:18.065
I WORK HARD,
I PRAY HARD.

03:20.000 --> 03:23.170
EVERYTHING IN MY LIFE
IS HARD.

03:25.272 --> 03:28.241
COME AND GET YOUR PACKETS
FOR SATURDAY'S WALKATHON.

03:28.241 --> 03:30.243
AND, PLEASE, NO RUNNING.

03:35.115 --> 03:36.349
GET IT?

03:36.349 --> 03:38.118
NO.

03:38.118 --> 03:42.055
ANY CHANCE
YOU COULD <i>WALK</i> ME THROUGH IT?

03:45.192 --> 03:47.994
REMEMBER, THIS IS TO RAISE MONEY
FOR THE LESS FORTUNATE,

03:47.994 --> 03:51.231
WHICH, IN MR. CULPEPPER'S CASE,
IS EVERYBODY.

03:51.231 --> 03:54.101
EVERY MILE
PUTS FOOD ON THEIR TABLES,

03:54.101 --> 03:57.237
PLACES ROOFS OVER THEIR HEADS,
AND POOLS IN THEIR BACKYARDS.

03:57.237 --> 03:59.039
YES.

03:59.039 --> 04:00.273
YOU DO SEE
A LOT OF POOR PEOPLE

04:00.273 --> 04:02.175
HOLDING
"WILL WORK FOR POOL" SIGNS.

04:04.010 --> 04:05.145
HOW ARE WE DOING?

04:05.145 --> 04:07.214
MAKING A BETTER TOMORROW
FOR EVERYBODY?

04:07.214 --> 04:08.281
UH, LOOKS LIKE IT.

04:08.281 --> 04:10.016
YOU KNOW, I NEVER PEGGED YOU
AS SOMEONE

04:10.016 --> 04:12.018
THAT WOULD GIVE BACK
TO THE COMMUNITY.

04:12.018 --> 04:13.120
I HEAR YOU.

04:13.120 --> 04:14.221
PEOPLE CALL ME A MONSTER

04:14.221 --> 04:16.990
BECAUSE I REPRESENT
THE POWERFUL AND THE WEALTHY,

04:16.990 --> 04:19.359
AND OFTEN
AT THE EXPENSE OF POOR PEOPLE.

04:22.262 --> 04:24.197
"MONSTER"
IS SUCH A STRONG WORD.

04:24.197 --> 04:27.968
LET'S GO WITH
"GREEDY BAD GUY."

04:27.968 --> 04:32.339
MM, I THINK I PREFER THE TERM
"WEALTH UNDISTRIBUTOR." YEAH.

04:32.339 --> 04:36.109
IT'S -- YOU SEE, THAT'S WHY
THIS FUNDRAISER IS SO IMPORTANT,

04:36.109 --> 04:38.178
'CAUSE I'VE GOT TO SHOW
THAT I REALLY CARE

04:38.178 --> 04:40.113
ABOUT THE LITTLE PEOPLE.

04:40.113 --> 04:41.148
YOU KNOW,
A GOOD WAY TO START

04:41.148 --> 04:43.316
IS TO NOT CALL THEM
"LITTLE PEOPLE."

04:45.085 --> 04:46.219
CHECK IT OUT.

04:46.219 --> 04:49.189
NEW PAIR OF SNEAKERS,
SOME PROTEIN PACKS.

04:49.189 --> 04:51.057
I GOT A REAL SHOT
AT WINNING THIS THING.

04:51.057 --> 04:53.994
JOSH, IT'S A WALKATHON,
NOT A RACE.

04:53.994 --> 04:57.130
WELL, WHEN IT COMES TO WALKING,
YOU DON'T WANT TO STEP TO ME.

05:00.167 --> 05:02.302
DID I JUST TALK TRASH?

05:02.302 --> 05:05.071
WELL,
IT SOUNDED LIKE <i>GARBAGE.</i>

05:05.071 --> 05:06.106
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:08.041 --> 05:10.043
IT'S JUST THAT,
EVER SINCE I WAS 2 YEARS OLD,

05:10.043 --> 05:11.178
I'VE BEEN
AN EXCELLENT WALKER.

05:11.178 --> 05:13.213
YEAH, WE ALL HAVE.

05:13.213 --> 05:15.081
Trent:
WHAT THE HELL?!

05:15.081 --> 05:17.284
MADDIE, GET IN HERE NOW!

05:17.284 --> 05:19.019
OHH.

05:19.019 --> 05:22.088
LOOKS LIKE
SOMEBODY'S GETTING A RAISE!

05:28.128 --> 05:32.065
A FRIEND IN THE MEDIA
SENT ME THIS.

05:32.065 --> 05:35.001
<i>HEY, BETCHES!</i>

05:35.001 --> 05:36.269
<i>BORED AT WORK?</i>

05:36.269 --> 05:39.072
<i>WELL, ALWAYS REMEMBER</i>
<i>TO HAVE</i>

05:39.072 --> 05:42.309
<i>THE PROPER TOPCOAT/HARDENER,</i>
<i>HMM?</i>

05:42.309 --> 05:43.243
<i>HEY!</i>

05:43.243 --> 05:44.311
<i>MS. GLORIA ALL-BROWN,</i>

05:44.311 --> 05:46.146
<i>WHEN YOU WAKE UP</i>
<i>FROM YOUR SIESTA,</i>

05:46.146 --> 05:49.049
<i>I'M GONNA NEED</i>
<i>THAT BRIEF.</i>

05:49.049 --> 05:51.051
<i>HOW SICK IS THAT?!</i>

05:51.051 --> 05:52.252
[ GIGGLES ]

05:56.122 --> 05:58.158
WOW.

05:58.158 --> 06:01.261
YOU COME ACROSS
PRETTY BAD.

06:01.261 --> 06:03.196
CARE TO EXPLAIN THIS?

06:03.196 --> 06:05.198
WELL, I DIDN'T KNOW
YOU WERE THERE.

06:05.198 --> 06:07.267
[ GASPS ] OH,
NOW I UNDERSTAND THE COMMENTS.

06:07.267 --> 06:11.238
OF COURSE
MY NAILS AREN'T RACIST.

06:11.238 --> 06:14.174
I HAVE SEEN
TOO MANY GOOD MEN'S LIVES

06:14.174 --> 06:16.209
RUINED BY A CARELESS REMARK.

06:16.209 --> 06:20.981
I AM NOT GONNA HAVE MY LEGACY
TARNISHED BY ONE HILARIOUS QUIP.

06:20.981 --> 06:22.315
OKAY, I'M SORRY, DADDY.
HOW CAN I FIX THIS?

06:22.315 --> 06:24.117
NO, NO, NO, NO.
YOU HAVE DONE ENOUGH.

06:24.117 --> 06:25.285
NOW I'VE GOT TO
FIGURE OUT A WAY

06:25.285 --> 06:29.122
TO GET MY ONE OFF-WHITE EMPLOYEE
TO PROVE I'M NOT RACIST.

06:31.124 --> 06:34.194
I-IS IT EVEN OKAY TO SAY
"OFF-WHITE"?

06:34.194 --> 06:37.163
I MEAN,
I DON'T EVEN KNOW ANYMORE.

06:39.099 --> 06:41.067
CRIS, GOOD NEWS.

06:41.067 --> 06:42.335
YOU'RE GONNA BE
MY CO-CHAIR FOR THE WALKATHON.

06:42.335 --> 06:44.304
I WANT YOU
UP THERE ON THE PODIUM

06:44.304 --> 06:46.273
FOR THE PRESS CONFERENCE,
OKAY?

06:46.273 --> 06:50.977
JUST WEAR SOMETHING THAT SAYS
"MY BOSS ISN'T A RACIST," OKAY?

06:50.977 --> 06:53.980
SO A PONCHO?

06:53.980 --> 06:58.051
UH, YOUR CHOICE, NOT MINE.
GREAT IDEA.

06:58.051 --> 06:59.152
THE THING'S AT 2:00.

06:59.152 --> 07:01.054
WAIT -- NO, 2:00?

07:01.054 --> 07:03.023
THAT'S THE SAME TIME
AS MY NEPHEW'S CONFIRMATION.

07:03.023 --> 07:05.191
OH, WELL, THAT'S
THE NICE THING ABOUT PONCHOS.

07:05.191 --> 07:07.193
YOU KNOW,
YOU CAN WEAR THEM ANYWHERE.

07:07.193 --> 07:12.999
SIR, UM,
ABOUT THE PRESS CONFERENCE...

07:12.999 --> 07:15.035
WHY WOULD THERE BE ONE?

07:15.035 --> 07:16.136
DAMAGE CONTROL.

07:16.136 --> 07:20.140
THERE'S A VIDEO OUT THERE
OF ME SAYING A JOKE TO YOU.

07:20.140 --> 07:21.274
WHAT AM I DOING?

07:21.274 --> 07:24.210
WASHING DISHING?
PARKING CARS? THE USUAL?

07:26.046 --> 07:28.048
YOU WERE
TAKING A SIESTA.

07:28.048 --> 07:30.250
OH, I REMEMBER THAT.
THAT WAS A GOOD ONE!

07:30.250 --> 07:34.020
YEAH,
I THOUGHT SO, TOO.

07:34.020 --> 07:36.990
SO, HOW IMPORTANT
IS THIS PRESS CONFERENCE?

07:36.990 --> 07:40.026
'CAUSE IT'S AT THE SAME TIME
AS MY NEPHEW'S CONFIRMATION.

07:40.026 --> 07:42.062
AAH, YOU CAN GO
TO THE NEXT ONE.

07:44.064 --> 07:47.133
ACTUALLY, IT'S A CEREMONY
THAT ONLY HAPPENS ONCE.

07:47.133 --> 07:50.003
IT'S NOT LIKE A MARRIAGE.
[ LAUGHS ]

07:54.007 --> 07:56.276
IS THERE ANY WAY WE CAN MOVE
THE PRESS CONFERENCE?

07:56.276 --> 08:00.280
HEY, WE COULD HAVE IT LATER,
AT A BAR, HUH?

08:00.280 --> 08:02.048
YOU'D LIKE IT.

08:02.048 --> 08:03.149
OH, YEAH.

08:03.149 --> 08:06.019
YEAH, 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS
A BETTER MAN WHEN I'M DRUNK.

08:06.019 --> 08:07.253
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:07.253 --> 08:10.256
YOU KNOW, I-I NEVER REALIZED
THAT YOU WERE SO RELIGIOUS.

08:10.256 --> 08:11.324
YEAH.

08:11.324 --> 08:14.060
I GO TO CHURCH TWICE A YEAR,
WHEN IT MATTERS.

08:15.328 --> 08:18.198
BIRTH OF JESUS,
DEATH OF JESUS.

08:18.198 --> 08:21.201
AND IN BETWEEN,
THE PLAYOFFS HAPPEN.

08:21.201 --> 08:25.038
WORK IS MY RELIGION,
AND IT SHOULD BE YOURS, TOO.

08:25.038 --> 08:28.108
CRISTELA,
YOU'RE A LOT LIKE ME.

08:28.108 --> 08:30.310
AND YOU KNOW THAT YOU'VE GOT
TO MAKE SOME SACRIFICES

08:30.310 --> 08:31.978
TO GET TO THE TOP.

08:31.978 --> 08:35.215
BUT THIS CONFIRMATION
IS A SPECIAL MOMENT.

08:35.215 --> 08:38.251
YEAH, WELL, THAT'S WHY
THEY CALL IT A "SACRIFICE."

08:39.252 --> 08:41.087
YOUR FAMILY
WILL GET OVER IT.

08:41.087 --> 08:43.189
I MEAN, IF YOU'RE SERIOUS
ABOUT YOUR CAREER,

08:43.189 --> 08:45.225
YOU'VE GOT TO BE SELFISH.

08:45.225 --> 08:49.062
SO, I'LL BE SELFISH...

08:49.062 --> 08:52.132
AND DO THIS FOR <i>YOU?</i>

08:52.132 --> 08:53.366
GREAT.

08:53.366 --> 08:57.971
I DON'T THINK YOU KNOW
WHAT THE WORD "SELFISH" MEANS.

08:57.971 --> 09:00.173
AWW, THANK YOU.

09:07.313 --> 09:10.984
WHAT IS TAKING
THAT BOY SO LONG?

09:10.984 --> 09:13.019
I THOUGHT <i>I</i> LOVED MIRRORS.

09:13.019 --> 09:14.120
YOU DO.

09:14.120 --> 09:15.088
AND YOU SHOULD.

09:15.088 --> 09:17.157
MM.

09:17.157 --> 09:19.225
HENRY, FOR EVERY SECOND
YOU MAKE GOD WAIT,

09:19.225 --> 09:23.029
HE MAKES YOU WAIT
A <i>YEAR</i> IN PURGATORY.

09:25.298 --> 09:27.167
ONE.

09:27.167 --> 09:28.134
TWO.

09:28.134 --> 09:30.103
Henry:
OKAY, I'M COMING!

09:30.103 --> 09:31.071
THERE HE IS!

09:31.071 --> 09:33.039
Daniela: [ GASPS ]
<i>QUé GUAPO!</i>

09:33.039 --> 09:34.340
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

09:36.142 --> 09:39.112
I AM READY TO DROP THE MIKE
ON MY CHILDHOOD.

09:39.112 --> 09:40.080
BAM!

09:42.315 --> 09:46.086
THEN MAYBE IT'S TIME
TO LOSE THE SUPERMAN UNDERWEAR.

09:48.354 --> 09:50.290
CRIS, LOOK.

09:50.290 --> 09:54.060
DOESN'T HENRY LOOK GREAT
IN HIS CONFIRMATION SUIT?

09:54.060 --> 09:55.295
WOW.

09:55.295 --> 09:57.163
IS THAT ALL
YOU CAN TALK ABOUT?

09:58.364 --> 10:01.067
MAKES ME NOT WANT TO GO.

10:02.335 --> 10:05.071
HENRY, GO CHANGE.

10:05.071 --> 10:08.074
I DON'T WANT YOU
TO RUIN THAT 50-YEAR-OLD SUIT.

10:08.074 --> 10:10.276
CRIS,
WHAT IS WRONG?

10:10.276 --> 10:14.214
LOOK, YOU'RE NOT
GONNA LIKE THIS...

10:14.214 --> 10:16.049
BUT I CAN'T GO
TO HENRY'S CONFIRMATION.

10:16.049 --> 10:17.183
AND, PLEASE,
DON'T START WITH ME

10:17.183 --> 10:19.018
BECAUSE I ALREADY
FEEL TERRIBLE ABOUT IT.

10:19.018 --> 10:20.286
YOU SHOULD.
<i>AMA!</i>

10:20.286 --> 10:22.122
WHAT?
YOU SHOULD FEEL TERRIBLE.

10:22.122 --> 10:23.356
AND IF YOU WERE
A REAL CATHOLIC,

10:23.356 --> 10:25.225
YOU'D KNOW
THAT'S WHAT WE DO.

10:27.026 --> 10:28.361
WELL, I HAVE TO WORK.

10:28.361 --> 10:30.230
AND I'VE MADE MY DECISION,

10:30.230 --> 10:32.999
AND THAT'S JUST
THE WAY IT'S GONNA HAVE TO BE.

10:32.999 --> 10:34.100
DON'T PAY ATTENTION
TO <i>AMA.</i>

10:34.100 --> 10:36.102
HAVING TO WORK
DOESN'T MAKE YOU A BAD CATHOLIC.

10:36.102 --> 10:38.138
IT MAKES YOU
A <i>BUSY</i> CATHOLIC.

10:38.138 --> 10:39.973
THANK YOU, DANIELA.

10:39.973 --> 10:41.341
I MEAN, LET'S FACE IT,
SINCE YOU'VE BEEN WORKING,

10:41.341 --> 10:43.243
WE'VE LEARNED NOT
TO EXPECT AS MUCH FROM YOU

10:43.243 --> 10:45.178
WHEN IT COMES TO FAMILY.

10:45.178 --> 10:49.048
THANK YOU A LITTLE LESS.

10:49.048 --> 10:51.151
I DON'T MEAN IT LIKE THAT.

10:51.151 --> 10:52.285
THE IMPORTANT THING IS

10:52.285 --> 10:55.054
THAT HENRY WILL HAVE
HIS CORE FAMILY THERE.

10:55.054 --> 10:57.190
NOW I TAKE BACK
THAT "THANK YOU."

10:58.358 --> 11:01.995
CORE FAMILY?

11:01.995 --> 11:03.062
WHAT AM I?

11:03.062 --> 11:05.031
YOU'RE <i>EXTENDED</i> FAMILY.

11:05.031 --> 11:06.332
LIKE <i>TIA SOCORRO.</i>

11:06.332 --> 11:09.035
SHE'S FAMILY,
BUT WE NEVER SEE HER.

11:09.035 --> 11:12.272
WELL, SHE'S DEAD.

11:17.177 --> 11:20.180
THE REFERRED TO THEMSELVES
AS "THE CORE FAMILY."

11:20.180 --> 11:22.148
HA HA HA! HUH?

11:23.316 --> 11:25.218
I'M IN THE CORE.

11:25.218 --> 11:27.053
I <i>AM</i> THE CORE.

11:27.053 --> 11:31.090
[ CHUCKLES ]
I USUALLY THROW AWAY THE CORE.

11:31.090 --> 11:33.059
IT JUST DOESN'T MAKE SENSE,
YOU KNOW?

11:33.059 --> 11:35.361
I MEAN, IT BOTHERED YOU
WHEN YOUR DAD WASN'T AROUND

11:35.361 --> 11:38.198
BECAUSE HE WAS ALWAYS
AT THE OFFICE, I MEAN, RIGHT?

11:38.198 --> 11:39.365
NO.

11:39.365 --> 11:41.000
WHY NOT?

11:41.000 --> 11:42.302
WELL,
I KNEW IF HE WASN'T AROUND,

11:42.302 --> 11:43.970
HE WAS MAKING MONEY

11:43.970 --> 11:45.171
SO I WOULDN'T HAVE TO WORK
A DAY IN MY LIFE.

11:45.171 --> 11:47.006
[ CHUCKLES ]

11:49.108 --> 11:50.310
YOU'RE WORKING RIGHT NOW.

11:50.310 --> 11:55.048
AM I, CRISTELA?

11:57.050 --> 11:59.185
SO, WAIT. I STILL DON'T
UNDERSTAND WHY YOU'RE UPSET.

11:59.185 --> 12:02.188
'CAUSE I'M MISSING STUFF,
AND THEY SHOULD FEEL BAD.

12:02.188 --> 12:05.091
'CAUSE I'M PART OF
THE CORE.

12:05.091 --> 12:08.094
AND <i>YOU</i> SHOULD FEEL BAD
BECAUSE YOUR DAD MISSED STUFF.

12:08.094 --> 12:09.128
WAIT.

12:09.128 --> 12:11.264
I'M TRYING
TO MAKE YOU FEEL BETTER,

12:11.264 --> 12:13.366
AND YOU'RE TRYING
TO MAKE ME FEEL <i>WORSE.</i>

12:13.366 --> 12:15.001
NO, I'M NOT. NO.

12:15.001 --> 12:16.135
Y-- I'M JUST,
YOU KNOW,

12:16.135 --> 12:18.071
I'M TRYING TO HELP YOU REALIZE
HOW MUCH YOU SUFFERED

12:18.071 --> 12:21.140
BY HAVING
THAT ABSENTEE FATHER.

12:21.140 --> 12:25.245
WELL, I-I NEVER THOUGHT ABOUT IT
LIKE THAT BEFORE.

12:25.245 --> 12:27.280
YEAH, WELL,
NOW THAT YOU THINK ABOUT IT,

12:27.280 --> 12:29.148
DON'T YOU KIND OF
RESENT HIM?

12:29.148 --> 12:31.050
YEAH.

12:31.050 --> 12:36.155
WOW, I HAVE A LOT OF PAIN
I DIDN'T KNOW ABOUT.

12:36.155 --> 12:38.057
I'M GLAD
I SAID SOMETHING.

12:38.057 --> 12:41.995
YEAH, I MEAN, HE WAS NEVER THERE
TO SHARE THOSE SPECIAL MOMENTS.

12:41.995 --> 12:43.129
WELL, I MEAN...

12:43.129 --> 12:45.198
IT WOULD HAVE BEEN OKAY
IF HE MISSED A FEW OF THEM.

12:45.198 --> 12:46.266
OH, I DON'T KNOW.

12:46.266 --> 12:48.134
I THINK OUR RELATIONSHIP
WOULD HAVE BEEN BETTER

12:48.134 --> 12:49.202
IF HE MADE ALL OF THEM.

12:49.202 --> 12:51.337
I MEAN, WHAT IF HE MISSED
THE MOST IMPORTANT ONE?

12:54.340 --> 12:55.341
GOOD POINT.

12:55.341 --> 12:58.144
MM-HMM.

12:58.144 --> 13:01.180
OH, NOW I FEEL BAD.

13:01.180 --> 13:02.982
YEAH.

13:02.982 --> 13:06.085
I GUESS WE BOTH HAVE A LOT OF
PAIN WE DIDN'T KNOW ABOUT, HMM?

13:07.987 --> 13:09.989
HMM. WELL, THIS WAS
A GOOD TALK, CRISTELA.

13:09.989 --> 13:11.057
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:11.057 --> 13:14.060
NO, IT WASN'T.

13:17.997 --> 13:19.999
I GOT TO GO, SIR.

13:19.999 --> 13:22.235
WHOA. WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.
WHAT ABOUT THE PRESS CONFERENCE?

13:22.235 --> 13:24.170
I CAN'T.

13:24.170 --> 13:27.273
I-I CAN'T MISS
THAT SPECIAL MOMENT.

13:27.273 --> 13:30.176
OKAY. FINE.
IT'S YOUR CHOICE.

13:30.176 --> 13:33.012
BUT, I GOT TO SAY,
IF YOU DECIDE TO LEAVE,

13:33.012 --> 13:35.381
IT WILL CHANGE
MY OPINION OF YOU.

13:38.251 --> 13:41.220
IS THERE ANY CHANCE
IT'LL CHANGE FOR THE BETTER?

13:51.137 --> 13:52.338
GREAT, GREAT.

13:52.338 --> 13:55.074
I GOT TO FACE
A ROOM FULL OF REPORTERS,

13:55.074 --> 13:57.276
AND MY MINORITY BEARD
JUST TOOK OFF.

14:00.313 --> 14:04.016
DON'T WORRY, DADDY.
I MEAN, I'M HERE FOR YOU.

14:04.016 --> 14:07.086
YEAH, WELL, NOTHING SAYS
"I'M MULTI-CULTURAL"

14:07.086 --> 14:11.023
LIKE MY RICH, BLOND,
NORDIC DAUGHTER.

14:11.023 --> 14:14.160
EVEN IF YOU WEREN'T THERE
FOR <i>ME.</i> [ CHUCKLES ]

14:14.160 --> 14:16.329
WELL, HANG ON.
WHAT'S THAT SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

14:16.329 --> 14:17.330
OH, NOTHING.

14:17.330 --> 14:18.364
YOU KNOW,
CRISTELA JUST POINTED OUT

14:18.364 --> 14:19.399
THAT YOU CARE
MORE ABOUT YOUR WORK THAN ME.

14:19.399 --> 14:20.366
ANYWAY, LET'S GO.

14:20.366 --> 14:22.368
NO, NO, NO. HOLD ON.
NO, NO.

14:22.368 --> 14:24.137
NO, WE NEED
TO TALK ABOUT THIS.

14:24.137 --> 14:26.105
NO, WE NEED
TO GO SAVE YOUR REPUTATION.

14:26.105 --> 14:27.373
WE'LL GET TO ME...

14:27.373 --> 14:29.242
PROBABLY NEVER.

14:29.242 --> 14:30.276
[ SIGHS ]

14:30.276 --> 14:33.045
CRISTELA,
THE GIFT THAT KEEPS ON GIVING.

14:41.087 --> 14:43.156
WERE YOU EXPECTING MORE?

14:43.156 --> 14:45.224
'CAUSE ONE GUY
DOESN'T SEEM LIKE A LOT.

14:48.060 --> 14:51.297
UH, EXCUSE ME, SHOULD WE WAIT
FOR YOUR COLLEAGUES TO SHOW UP?

14:51.297 --> 14:53.032
I WOULDN'T.

14:53.032 --> 14:56.169
"RICH, WHITE TEXAN IS A RACIST"
ISN'T EXACTLY NEWS.

14:58.204 --> 15:01.174
ME, I LOVE IT.
IT'S -- IT'S MY ANGLE.

15:01.174 --> 15:05.077
LOOK, MR. REPORTER,
MY DAD IS NOT A RACIST.

15:05.077 --> 15:08.014
I MEAN, YEAH, HE MAY SAY
THE OCCASIONAL RACIST THING,

15:08.014 --> 15:10.016
BUT THAT'S ONLY
BECAUSE HE'S OLD.

15:10.016 --> 15:14.120
WHY DON'T YOU WRITE DOWN
THAT SHE SAID "DISTINGUISHED"?

15:14.120 --> 15:15.154
SURE, YEAH.

15:15.154 --> 15:16.322
JUST LET ME --
LET ME WRITE THAT DOWN.

15:16.322 --> 15:19.325
J.K.
WE HAVEN'T USED PENS IN YEARS.

15:19.325 --> 15:21.327
YOU KNOW,
THAT'S JUST THE WAY

15:21.327 --> 15:24.130
PEOPLE OF HIS GENERATION TALK,
YOU KNOW?

15:24.130 --> 15:27.233
IT'S WHY HE SAYS
"CLICKER" AND "DUNGAREES."

15:29.035 --> 15:32.338
BUT HE'S A KINDHEARTED MAN WHO,
YOU KNOW, CARES ABOUT PEOPLE.

15:32.338 --> 15:34.273
YOU KNOW, AND,
AS HIS DAUGHTER,

15:34.273 --> 15:37.376
I KNOW HIM ALMOST AS WELL AS
EVERYBODY HE'S EVER WORKED WITH.

15:37.376 --> 15:40.246
COME ON, MADDIE.
YOU DON'T REALLY BELIEVE THAT.

15:40.246 --> 15:41.347
I DON'T KNOW.

15:41.347 --> 15:45.184
IT'S NOT LIKE YOU WERE
AROUND ALL THE TIME.

15:45.184 --> 15:46.252
WELL, BUT, I MEAN,

15:46.252 --> 15:49.155
I ONLY WORKED LONG HOURS
TO PROVIDE FOR YOU

15:49.155 --> 15:51.390
BECAUSE I LOVE YOU.

15:53.192 --> 15:57.063
EXCUSE ME [CHUCKLES] COULD WE
GET BACK TO THE RACIST THING

15:57.063 --> 16:02.201
AND THEN DEAL WITH
YOU BEING A BAD FATHER?

16:02.201 --> 16:05.104
NO, WE CANNOT.

16:05.104 --> 16:08.407
BECAUSE I DON'T WANT MY DAUGHTER
HERE TO THINK FOR ONE SECOND

16:08.407 --> 16:11.177
THAT ANY OF THIS
IS MORE IMPORTANT THAN SHE IS.

16:11.177 --> 16:13.279
SO, YOU --
YOU CAN WRITE WHATEVER YOU WANT.

16:13.279 --> 16:14.347
WE'RE WALKING OUT OF HERE.

16:14.347 --> 16:17.016
OH.

16:17.016 --> 16:20.219
AND THERE IS $100
ON THE PODIUM.

16:20.219 --> 16:21.420
WINK, WINK.

16:26.325 --> 16:30.162
WHO PUTS ON A SUIT THEN
DRINKS A BIG GLASS OF KOOL-AID?

16:30.162 --> 16:33.065
NOW HENRY'S SON
CAN'T WEAR IT.

16:33.065 --> 16:35.234
[ SIGHS ]
WHAT A TRAGEDY.

16:35.234 --> 16:36.302
[ CHURCH BELLS TOLL ]

16:36.302 --> 16:38.337
OH, LET'S GO.
IT'S ABOUT TO START.

16:38.337 --> 16:39.305
[ TOLLING CONTINUES ]

16:39.305 --> 16:41.307
WAIT! WAIT!
I'M HERE!

16:41.307 --> 16:43.009
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

16:43.009 --> 16:44.010
DID I MAKE IT?

16:44.010 --> 16:46.112
ARE THOSE BELLS?

16:46.112 --> 16:49.015
AM I DEAD?

16:49.015 --> 16:50.349
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

16:50.349 --> 16:54.186
I AM HERE FOR THE FAMILY
WHETHER YOU LIKE IT OR NOT.

16:54.186 --> 16:55.154
HA!

16:56.188 --> 16:58.057
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

16:58.057 --> 17:00.059
I'M TALKING ABOUT
HOW EASY IT WAS FOR YOU GUYS

17:00.059 --> 17:01.127
TO LET ME OFF THE HOOK.

17:01.127 --> 17:03.329
YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE
LOW EXPECTATIONS OF ME.

17:03.329 --> 17:05.364
YOU SHOULD HAVE
<i>HIGH</i> EXPECTATIONS.

17:05.364 --> 17:09.068
I MEAN,
WHO DO I THINK I AM?

17:10.102 --> 17:12.438
I'M NOT DEAD
LIKE <i>TIA SOCORRO.</i>

17:12.438 --> 17:16.208
I'M PART OF THE CORE FAMILY,
AND I WILL NOT BE THROWN AWAY!

17:16.208 --> 17:18.010
AND I HAVE MORE
TO SAY ABOUT THIS,

17:18.010 --> 17:20.246
BUT I THINK
I'M GONNA THROW UP.

17:22.281 --> 17:24.283
I'M HAPPY
YOU'RE HERE, CRIS.

17:24.283 --> 17:25.284
I'M NOT.

17:25.284 --> 17:27.320
YOU SEEM LIKE
YOU'RE IN A BAD MOOD.

17:27.320 --> 17:30.256
WELL, HOW WOULD YOU FEEL
IF YOU MISSED SOMETHING

17:30.256 --> 17:32.224
AND NO ONE
IN THE FAMILY CARED?

17:32.224 --> 17:34.160
WE <i>DO</i> CARE.

17:34.160 --> 17:35.361
I DIDN'T WANT YOU
TO FEEL BAD.

17:35.361 --> 17:38.297
SHE SHOULD FEEL
A <i>LITTLE</i> BAD.

17:40.066 --> 17:42.101
<i>AMA.</i>

17:42.101 --> 17:43.336
WE DIDN'T WANT
TO TELL YOU,

17:43.336 --> 17:46.172
BUT HENRY WAS REALLY UPSET
THAT YOU WOULDN'T HEAR

17:46.172 --> 17:48.140
THE CONFIRMATION NAME
THAT HE CHOSE.

17:48.140 --> 17:49.408
IT'S "CHRIS."

17:49.408 --> 17:54.213
AS IN "CHRISTOPHER"
BUT ALSO AS IN "CRISTELA."

17:54.213 --> 17:56.248
YEAH, SHE GETS IT.

17:58.351 --> 18:02.221
YOU PICKED A NAME
AFTER ME?

18:02.221 --> 18:05.257
EVEN THOUGH
I ALMOST DIDN'T MAKE IT HERE?

18:05.257 --> 18:07.059
YEAH.

18:07.059 --> 18:09.061
'CAUSE YOU ALWAYS
LOOK OUT FOR ME.

18:09.061 --> 18:12.098
AND I KNOW
IT SOUNDS CORNY,

18:12.098 --> 18:15.301
BUT I FEEL SAFE
WHEN YOU'RE AROUND.

18:15.301 --> 18:18.104
IT'S PART OF THE SPEECH
I'M GONNA GIVE.

18:20.106 --> 18:21.240
THAT'S SO SWEET.

18:23.275 --> 18:27.179
YOU KNOW THEY DON'T LET YOU
MAKE SPEECHES, RIGHT?

18:27.179 --> 18:31.250
WHEN I LOOK THIS GOOD,
I'M GONNA TALK.

18:31.250 --> 18:33.252
YOU DO LOOK GOOD.

18:33.252 --> 18:34.353
COVER THAT STAIN.

18:37.356 --> 18:40.159
[ LAUGHS ]

18:45.064 --> 18:46.298
Cristela: HEY, SIR.

18:46.298 --> 18:48.134
DID YOU HAVE
A NICE WEEKEND?

18:48.134 --> 18:50.336
[ SIGHS ]
WHAT DO YOU WANT, CRISTELA?

18:50.336 --> 18:52.271
WELL,
I TALKED TO MADDIE,

18:52.271 --> 18:55.174
AND IT SOUNDS LIKE
IT ALL TURNED OUT GREAT.

18:55.174 --> 18:57.076
HOW DO YOU FIGURE?

18:57.076 --> 18:58.177
I'M OUT 100 BUCKS,

18:58.177 --> 19:01.080
AND THE <i>FORT WORTH OBSERVER</i>
CALLED ME "OLD."

19:01.080 --> 19:05.251
HEY, "OLD" IS BETTER
THAN RACIST, HUH?

19:07.253 --> 19:10.056
BUT YOU HAD A GREAT CONVERSATION
WITH MADDIE,

19:10.056 --> 19:12.224
AND YOU CLEARED UP
ALL YOUR PROBLEMS.

19:12.224 --> 19:15.061
OH, THE -- THE ONES
THAT WE DIDN'T KNOW WE HAD

19:15.061 --> 19:17.063
UNTIL YOU POINTED THEM OUT?

19:17.063 --> 19:19.098
THEY WERE
STILL THERE, SIR.

19:19.098 --> 19:20.099
AH.

19:20.099 --> 19:24.070
AGAIN,
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

19:24.070 --> 19:27.306
JUST WANTED TO SEE
IF YOU WERE STILL MAD AT ME.

19:27.306 --> 19:29.075
AND I'M GUESSING...

19:29.075 --> 19:31.043
YES.

19:31.043 --> 19:34.013
OKAY.

19:34.013 --> 19:36.215
MAYBE I'M NOT LIKE YOU.

19:36.215 --> 19:37.283
I WANT TO GET TO THE TOP,

19:37.283 --> 19:42.021
BUT I STILL WANT TO BE THERE
FOR MY FAMILY.

19:42.021 --> 19:45.024
CRISTELA.

19:45.024 --> 19:46.025
[ SIGHS ]

19:46.025 --> 19:48.160
IT MAY HAVE
ALL WORKED OUT.

19:48.160 --> 19:53.199
BUT MY OPINION OF YOU
ISN'T WHAT IT WAS.

19:53.199 --> 19:56.102
I GET IT.

19:56.102 --> 19:58.337
BUT I'M STILL
WALKING OUT OF HERE

19:58.337 --> 20:02.208
KNOWING THAT I DID
THE RIGHT THING.

20:02.208 --> 20:06.178
AND I'M LEAVING 50 CENTS
ON THE DESK.

20:17.323 --> 20:18.357
WINK, WINK.

20:25.397 --> 20:27.266
HEY, BETCHES!

20:27.266 --> 20:29.168
[ LAUGHS ]
IT'S ME AGAIN.

20:29.168 --> 20:31.103
OKAY,
SO, PEOPLE ARE ALWAYS ASKING

20:31.103 --> 20:32.404
HOW TO MAKE YOUR LIPS POP.

20:32.404 --> 20:34.240
WELL, YOU KNOW,
PORCELAIN SKIN HELPS,

20:34.240 --> 20:37.343
BUT FOR THE LESS FORTUNATE,
TRY GLOSS, HMM?

20:37.343 --> 20:38.344
DID YOU HEAR, SIR?

20:38.344 --> 20:40.045
YOU'VE, UH,
YOU'VE BEEN NAMED

20:40.045 --> 20:41.213
ONE OF DALLAS'
TOP PHILANTHROPISTS.

20:41.213 --> 20:43.048
WELL, HEY,
THAT'S NO SURPRISE.

20:43.048 --> 20:45.017
I, UM --
I'VE BEEN KNOWN TO DONATE

20:45.017 --> 20:47.186
TO PEOPLE OF ALL COLORS
AND RACES AND ETHNICITIES.

20:47.186 --> 20:49.021
YOU'RE A --
A TRUE GENTLEMAN.

20:49.021 --> 20:50.322
AND --
AND SEXUAL ORIENTATIONS.

20:50.322 --> 20:51.357
WOW, THAT'S AMAZING.

20:51.357 --> 20:53.225
A-AND --
AND RELIGIONS, TOO.

20:53.225 --> 20:57.263
HELL, I-I'VE BLOWN MONEY CHARITY
LIKE SHE'S A HIGH-END ESCORT.

20:59.365 --> 21:02.067
WHAT? WHAT, WOMEN
ARE OUT-OF-BOUNDS, TOO?

21:02.067 --> 21:04.069
OH, MAN.
I GIVE UP!
